<item>
            <title>[LU-13959] lctl snapshot_list should allow --fsname to be optional</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-13959</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Consider:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
[root@mds1 ~]# lctl snapshot_list
The fsname must be specified
List the specified snapshot or all snapshots.
Usage:
snapshot_list [-d | --detail] &amp;lt;-F | --fsname fsname&amp;gt; [-h | --help] [-n | --name ssname] [-r | --rsh remote_shell]
Options:
-d: list every piece &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; the specified snapshot.
-F: the filesystem name.
-h: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; help information.
-n: the snapshot&apos;s name.
-r: the remote shell used &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; communication with remote target, the &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;default&lt;/span&gt; value is &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;ssh&apos;&lt;/span&gt;. &lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The &lt;tt&gt;--fs_name&lt;/tt&gt; flag should be optional. If not provided, all snapshots for all known filesystems should be listed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
